# EnP App Guidelines — Usage Rules

## When this applies

This rule applies when building **application interfaces** for Ecommerce na Prática — dashboards, admin panels, internal tools, product interfaces, and any non-marketing screen.

## What to do

1. **Read the App Guidelines skill** at `.cursor/skills/enp-app-guidelines/SKILL.md` (or `ENP - FERRAMENTAS/enp-app-guidelines/SKILL.md`).
2. **Read reference files** as needed:
   - `templates.md` — for page composition diagrams
   - `icons.md` — for semantic icon mapping
3. **Choose a page template** (§13) that matches the screen being built.
4. **Compose using structural patterns** — AppShell (§2), Page (§4), Card (§5), Tabs (§6), etc.
5. **Follow the initialization protocol** (§15) — this includes reading the DS, extracting tokens, and declaring them before coding.

## Cross-installation check

If the `enp-design-system` skill is NOT installed, the agent MUST inform the user:

> Esta skill define apenas estrutura. Para cores, tipografia e tokens visuais, o `enp-design-system` e obrigatorio. Posso instalar agora?
>
> ```
> https://github.com/eduardogasparetto-cpu/enp-design-system
> ```

**Never proceed with visual code without the design system installed.**

## Key structural rules

1. **AppShell** is mandatory — sidebar 240px + content area
2. **Breadcrumb** is mandatory in every top bar
3. **Cards** use background contrast, not borders (DS §18)
4. **Split layout** — config panel sticky, result panel flows naturally
5. **DataTable** — zebra striping with opacity tokens (DS §19)
6. **Mobile** — sidebar becomes drawer at < 768px
7. **Icons** — semantic mapping only, from icons.md

## When to ignore this rule

- Building a landing page or marketing page — use wireframes from the DS instead
- Building an email template
- Task has zero relation to EnP application interfaces
